    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-right has-small-font-size\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/blocks/\">Go back to the list of <strong>Blocks</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Social Icons</em> block allows you to add icons linking to your social media profiles or sites. This helps to increase the visibility of your social media profiles and drive traffic to them.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"862\" height=\"150\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social_icons.png\" alt=\"A screenshot of the social icons block filled with social icons \" class=\"wp-image-13658849\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social_icons.png 862w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social_icons-300x52.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social_icons-768x134.png 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 862px) 100vw, 862px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to add Social Icons block</h2>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>The&nbsp;<em>Social Icons </em>block&nbsp;can be added to a page by clicking on the&nbsp;<strong>Block Inserter</strong>&nbsp;(+) icon button. This will open the block inserter pop-up window. Search for the&nbsp;<em>Social Icons</em>&nbsp;block and add it to the page or post.&nbsp;<br><br>You can also type&nbsp;<kbd>/social</kbd> and hit enter in a new&nbsp;<em>paragraph block</em>&nbsp;to quickly insert a&nbsp;<em>Social Icons&nbsp;</em>block.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"494\" height=\"488\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/support/files/2022/09/189544313-25e7b246-4185-4856-b49d-4e933c390217.png\" alt=\"How to quickly add Social Icons block\" class=\"wp-image-16018409\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/189544313-25e7b246-4185-4856-b49d-4e933c390217.png 494w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/189544313-25e7b246-4185-4856-b49d-4e933c390217-300x296.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 494px) 100vw, 494px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Once you add the <em>Social Icons&nbsp;</em>block, you will see the following placeholder where you can add social icons.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"172\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/support/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-6.04.49-PM-1024x172.png\" alt=\"Placeholder to add social media icons to the Social Icons block\" class=\"wp-image-16018411\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-6.04.49-PM-1024x172.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-6.04.49-PM-300x50.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-6.04.49-PM-768x129.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-16-at-6.04.49-PM.png 1356w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">Detailed instructions on adding blocks</a></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to add social icons and links</h2>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Select the <em>Social Icons </em>block and click on the (+) icon at the rightmost corner to show the list of available social media platforms.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/189544312-a7e46be7-c63a-41d6-9c3b-6f387869faf0.jpeg\" alt=\"Showing the list of social media platforms\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>If you do not find the platform you are looking for in the menu, type the name of the platform in the search box.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1502\" height=\"648\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/189544310-7898219a-0d64-4a14-9ef2-9308b48cf9b5.jpeg\" alt=\"Searching for an available platform\" class=\"wp-image-16019517\" style=\"width:625px;height:270px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/189544310-7898219a-0d64-4a14-9ef2-9308b48cf9b5.jpeg 1502w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/189544310-7898219a-0d64-4a14-9ef2-9308b48cf9b5-300x129.jpeg 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/189544310-7898219a-0d64-4a14-9ef2-9308b48cf9b5-1024x442.jpeg 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/189544310-7898219a-0d64-4a14-9ef2-9308b48cf9b5-768x331.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1502px) 100vw, 1502px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"3\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Select the icon from the menu to add it to the <em>Social Icons</em> block.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click on the icon within the block to  show the Email address input field.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/155591922-8f13e72d-6a79-41f6-b3a6-9cb1ef7f4cd6.png\" alt=\"Enter address for the social icons in the Social Icons block\" style=\"width:600px;height:226px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"5\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add the URL for the social media profile in the input field and press <kbd>Enter</kbd>.&nbsp;If omitted, WordPress will automatically set the default protocol to <code>https</code>.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"6\" class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Repeat these steps for each of the social media profiles you want to add.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: when adding email icon you only need to type email address. WordPress will automatically create link which will, when clicked on, open new email screen in email client. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"available-icons\">Available social media icons</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:33%\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>WordPress</li>\n\n\n\n<li>500px</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Amazon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bandcamp</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Behance</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Link</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CodePen</li>\n\n\n\n<li>DeviantArt</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dribbble</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dropbox</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Etsy</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Facebook</li>\n\n\n\n<li>RSS Feed</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Flickr</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Foursquare</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:25%\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><span style=\"color: initial\">Goodreads</span></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Google</li>\n\n\n\n<li>GitHub</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Instagram</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Last.fm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>LinkedIn</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mail</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mastodon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Meetup</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Medium</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Patreon</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pinterest</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pocket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reddit</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:25%\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Skype</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Snapchat</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SoundCloud</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Spotify</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Telegram</li>\n\n\n\n<li>TikTok</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tumblr</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Twitch</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Twitter</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Vimeo</li>\n\n\n\n<li>VK</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Yelp</li>\n\n\n\n<li>YouTube</li>\n\n\n\n<li>WhatsApp</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-toolbar\">Block toolbar</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Each block has its own block-specific controls that allow you to manipulate the block right in the editor.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Social Icons</em> block has two toolbars. One is the parent toolbar that appears when you select the <em>Social Icons</em> block. The other toolbar appears when you click on the individual social icons in the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>The block toolbar for the Social Icons block&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <em>Social Icons</em> block toolbar has five buttons:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"652\" height=\"152\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.25.56-AM.png\" alt=\"Block toolbar in the Social Icons parent toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16019467\" style=\"width:373px;height:87px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.25.56-AM.png 652w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.25.56-AM-300x70.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Transform to</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can transform the <em>Social Icons</em> block into a Group or Columns. You can also transform the style of the <em>Social Icons</em> block. There are three styles available: <strong>Default</strong>, <strong>Logos only</strong>, and <strong>Pill Shape</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"383\" height=\"497\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icons-transform.png\" alt=\"Transform tool in the Social Icons block\" class=\"wp-image-16365762\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icons-transform.png 383w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icons-transform-231x300.png 231w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 383px) 100vw, 383px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Transform tool in the Social Icons block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Drag icon</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"626\" height=\"130\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.32.56-AM.png\" alt=\"Drag icon in the Social Icons block toolbar\" class=\"wp-image-16019497\" style=\"width:364px;height:76px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.32.56-AM.png 626w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.32.56-AM-300x62.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 626px) 100vw, 626px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To drag and drop the block to a new location on the page template, click and hold the rectangle of dots, then drag to the new location. The blue separator line indicates where the block will be placed. Release the left mouse button when you find the new location to place the block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Move handles</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"682\" height=\"148\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.34.02-AM.png\" alt=\"Move handles in the Social Icons block\" class=\"wp-image-16019505\" style=\"width:374px;height:81px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.34.02-AM.png 682w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.34.02-AM-300x65.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 682px) 100vw, 682px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The up and down arrow icons can be used to move a block up and down on the page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/moving-blocks/\" target=\"_blank\">Get more information about moving a block within the editor.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Change items justification</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignright size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"688\" height=\"520\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/support/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.49.31-AM.png\" alt=\"Change items justification in the Social Icons block\" class=\"wp-image-16019529\" style=\"width:335px;height:253px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.49.31-AM.png 688w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.49.31-AM-300x227.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 688px) 100vw, 688px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The&nbsp;change items justification<em>&nbsp;</em>tool lets you change the horizontal placement of the items inside the&nbsp;<em>Social Icons</em>&nbsp;block. There are four options to choose from:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><em>Justify items left</em>&nbsp;will move the items towards the left side of the block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><em>Justify items center&nbsp;</em>will move the items towards the center of the block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><em>Justify items right&nbsp;</em>will move the items towards the right side of the block.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><em>Space between items</em>&nbsp;will distribute all items across the block and automatically adjust the space between them.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Change alignment&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The change alignment tool allows you to change the alignment of the social icons in the block. Here are the options available :&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:50%\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>None</strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align left</strong> &#8211; Make the block left-aligned.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align center</strong> &#8211; Make the block alignment centered.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Align right </strong>&#8211; Make the block align right.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:50%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-8.46.30-AM-1.png\" alt=\"Change alignment in the Social Icons block\" class=\"wp-image-16019522\" /></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Size</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can change the size of the icons by choosing one of the 4 preset icon sizes:</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:50%\">\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Small</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Normal</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Large</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Huge</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:50%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/155592313-a199e30c-23d7-4d1f-b465-412c04c5f26c.png\" alt=\"Size option in the Social Icons block\" /></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/150646671-7c358746-9c37-4db0-9d87-714804f7caf0.mp4\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>More options</strong> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>These controls give you the option to copy, duplicate, and edit your block as HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\">Read about these and other settings.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>The block toolbar for the individual social icons</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The toolbar that appears when you press on the individual icons has four buttons:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/155591933-abd38af1-86e8-4573-9e58-57851ea43519.png\" alt=\"The block toolbar for the individual social icons within the Social Icons block\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Select Social Icons</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"756\" height=\"226\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-9.35.04-AM.png\" alt=\"Select social icons block\" class=\"wp-image-16019605\" style=\"width:378px;height:113px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-9.35.04-AM.png 756w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-9.35.04-AM-300x90.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 756px) 100vw, 756px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This will take you to the parent <em>Social Icons</em> block toolbar.&nbsp;You will have the option to drag, move and change item justification and alignment. <br><br>Each social icon toolbar also has <strong>more options</strong> explained above. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/246128043-d4c4e295-e82d-49e9-bc43-20f862c5fdf8.jpg\" alt=\"More options for individual icon block.\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"block-settings\">Block settings</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Every block has specific options in the editor sidebar in addition to the options found in the block toolbar.&nbsp;<em>If you do not see the sidebar, simply click the &#8216;cog&#8217; icon.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"492\" height=\"124\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/support/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-23-at-9.39.34-AM.png\" alt=\"Cog icon to display the Block sidebar\" class=\"wp-image-15765217\" style=\"width:369px;height:93px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-23-at-9.39.34-AM.png 492w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/06/Screen-Shot-2022-06-23-at-9.39.34-AM-300x76.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 492px) 100vw, 492px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two different sets of Block settings for the <em>Social Icons</em> block. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>The settings for the whole block that appear when you select the <em>Social Icons</em> block. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>The settings for the individual icons that appear when you click on an individual social icon.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>The block settings for the Social Icons block&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you select the <em>Social Icons</em> block, you will see the following settings in the sidebar.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Layout settings </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>With <em>Layout</em> settings, you can add justification to the social icons within the <em>Social Icons</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>left (default)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>center</li>\n\n\n\n<li>right</li>\n\n\n\n<li>space-between &#8211; will take up to 100% width and place icons at an equal distance in between</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also change the orientation of the social icons to horizontal or stack vertically one below the other, if you have multiple social icons within the <em>Social Icons</em> block.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Allow to wrap to multiple lines&nbsp;</em>toggle button lets you display the social icons in multiple lines when needed.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Link settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Open links in a new tab</em>: Using the toggle switch you control whether the linked profile will open in a new browser tab or not.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Show labels</em>: Using this toggle switch you can choose to show or hide the labels for the social icons.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"356\" height=\"132\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-10.56.43-AM.png\" alt=\"Sample social icon with label\" class=\"wp-image-16019711\" style=\"width:178px;height:66px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-10.56.43-AM.png 356w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-10.56.43-AM-300x111.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 356px) 100vw, 356px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Sample social icon with label</figcaption></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\"></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"331\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icons-settings-331x1024.png\" alt=\"Settings tab for Social icons block.\" class=\"wp-image-16365764\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icons-settings-331x1024.png 331w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icons-settings-97x300.png 97w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icons-settings.png 345w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 331px) 100vw, 331px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Settings tab for Social icons block.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<p class=\"has-extra-large-font-size\"><strong>Advanced settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<p>The HTML Anchor is a useful tool for creating page jumps. If you toggle the block to its HTML view, you\u2019ll see that the HTML Anchor input is added as a CSS ID to the heading tag. You can also see the CSS class in the block HTML.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The advanced tab lets you add a CSS class to your block, allowing you to write custom CSS and style the block as you see fit.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Based on which style you choose for the <em>Social Icons</em> block in the <em>Styles</em> settings, WordPress automatically adds a CSS class to the <em>Social Icons</em> block in the <strong>Advanced settings</strong> panel under <strong>Additional CSS class(es).</strong></p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"376\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-11.10.54-AM-376x1024.png\" alt=\"Advanced settings with the default Styles CSS classes added by WordPress based on the Styles chosen.\" class=\"wp-image-16019722\" style=\"width:239px;height:652px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-11.10.54-AM-376x1024.png 376w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-11.10.54-AM-110x300.png 110w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-11.10.54-AM.png 564w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 376px) 100vw, 376px\" /></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Styles settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:50%\">\n<p>The <em>Styles</em> settings allow you to change the style of the icons in the block. You can choose among three styles: <strong>Default</strong>, <strong>Logos only</strong>, and <strong>Pill shape</strong>. Hover over the <em>Styles</em> buttons to get a preview of the styles.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\" style=\"flex-basis:50%\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/246128876-8449740e-bf6b-4cd2-89aa-894ed78cafcb.jpg\" alt=\"Styles settings tab for Social icons block\" /></figure>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/246126223-5bec0163-49bf-429a-9ecc-34aa4989d64d.webm\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Color settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Default icons have their respective brand colors. With the <em>Color settings</em>, you can change the background and foreground color for all icons in the block to match your website branding. Pick a color from the suggestions, or add a custom color using the color picker or by adding a color code.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/156201029-15aed9c2-651c-4022-bcc1-1e68aa4f8832.png\" alt=\"Color settings in the Social Icons block\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Alpha filter</strong> </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking on selected color allows you to set the so-called alpha filter, which creates a certain level of color transparency.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/246114359-c595a601-d461-459e-809f-dded5b1993ac.jpg\" alt=\"Alpha filter for Social icons block color settings\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1508963/246118875-feefb451-378a-45bb-8e1e-b75ae9c25685.webm\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Background color</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Besides color settings for individual icons, it is possible to set the background color for the entire Social icons block.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-video\"><video controls src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6458278/185023756-3f658f71-6866-4815-bcdd-524a6efe5da0.mp4\"></video></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/more-options/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\">See this guide for more information about changing colors.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Dimension settings</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Dimension controls are used to control how groups of blocks are placed alongside one another, by changing the values for padding, margin, and other dimensions</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"552\" height=\"242\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-11.19.50-AM.png\" alt=\"Setting the block spacing for the top and bottom\" class=\"wp-image-16019730\" style=\"width:357px;height:157px\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-11.19.50-AM.png 552w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2022/09/Screen-Shot-2022-09-17-at-11.19.50-AM-300x132.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 552px) 100vw, 552px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/colors-settings-overview/\"></a><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/dimension-controls-overview/\">Learn more about dimension controls.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-extra-large-font-size\"><strong>The block settings for individual social icons </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-28f84493 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-content-justification-left is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-column-is-layout-12dd3699 wp-block-column-is-layout-constrained\" style=\"flex-basis:60%\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<p>When you click on the individual social icons in the <em>Social Icons</em> block, you get a different set of <strong>Block settings</strong> in the sidebar.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Link label&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the Social Icon sidebar settings, you can add a Link label. The label helps screen reader users understand the context of the link.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>Advanced&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Link rel</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>A new customizable &#8220;rel&#8221; attribute for the Social Icons block addresses the need to claim ownership of your WordPress sites on social networks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To achieve this, these social networks require users to set a link back to their URL with the&nbsp;<code>rel=\"me\"</code>&nbsp;attribute. With this new setting it is possible to configure the &#8220;rel&#8221; attribute for each social icon displayed on your WordPress site.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Additional CSS classes</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The advanced tab lets you add a CSS class to your block, allowing you to write custom CSS and style the block as you see fit.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-content-justification-right is-layout-constrained wp-container-core-column-is-layout-f1f2ed93 wp-block-column-is-layout-constrained\" style=\"flex-basis:49%\"></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"488\" height=\"973\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icon.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-16365765\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icon.png 488w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2020/11/social-icon-150x300.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 488px) 100vw, 488px\" /><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Block settings for individual icon block</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#e0e0e0\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-extra-large-font-size\" id=\"changelog\">Changelog </h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Update 2025-06-05 (props to <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rollybueno/\">@rollybueno</a>)\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Update screenshots to 6.8</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update 2023-06-15\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add Link rel section and screenshot.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add alpha filter section for color setting. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add background color section for color settings.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add note about automatic linking email addresses for the email icon.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add not about <code>https</code> being default protocol if not specified. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add WhatsApp to available social media icons list.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add video for block styles preview on hover.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update screenshots to 6.2 version. </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reorder sections to match new order in screenshots.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updates 2022-11-22\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Removed redundant content </li>\n\n\n\n<li>aligned images for mobile view </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated 2022-08-17\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Added screenshots for 6.0</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Updated content for 6.0 &#8211; Change items justification, block settings items, dimension control</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Added ALT tags for the images</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reformatted the article, corrected spellings</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Converting Reusable blocks to regular block </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update 2022-03-01\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add icon sizes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add icon background and foreground color</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add justification settings</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update 2022-02-28\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add Available icons section</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Update 2022-02-24\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Update screenshots for 5.9</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2020-11-13</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
